title: Choosing Our Enemies
new-page: true
view-if: (year <= 1932 and enemies_timer <= 0) or (sandbox = 1 and enemies_timer <= 0)
on-arrival: month_actions += 1; enemies_timer = 12; enemies_timer = 10 if sandbox = 1
is-card: true
card-image: img/poster_1.png
tags: party_affairs

= Choosing our enemies

In our media and campaign materials, who should we consider as our main opponents (workers and unemployed will be affected)? Keep in mind, a consolidated base of the radical parties won't leave its party so easily.
[? if enemies != 0: Previously, we had considered the [+ enemies +] as our prior enemies. Is a change of direction necessary? ?]

- @anti_dem: The anti-democratic parties of the far right and left – the KPD, NSDAP, and DNVP.
- @far_right: The far right – the NSDAP and DNVP.
- @dnvp: The DNVP alone.
- @nsdap: The NSDAP alone.
- @kpd: The KPD.
- @bourgeois: The bourgeois parties – the Center and DVP.
- @dvp: The DVP party.
- @easy_discard

@anti_dem
on-arrival: enemies = "anti-democratic parties"; center_strength += 5; reformist_strength += 5; left_dissent += 5; workers_kpd -= 2; workers_nsdap -= 2; workers_dnvp -= 2; kpd_relation -= 10

Attacking the far right and left is popular among all but the left wing of our party, who would prefer fighting the bourgeois parties. This might also hamper our ability to reconcile with the KPD in the future.

@far_right
on-arrival: enemies = "far right"; left_strength += 5; left_dissent -= 5; workers_nsdap -= 2 if workers_nsdap < 20; workers_dnvp -= 4

Attacking the far right is popular among the entire party, although the left considers the bourgeois parties just as dangerous, while the right criticizes our lack of response to the KPD. Our bourgeois coalition partners are skeptical of our commitment to anti-communism.

@dnvp
on-arrival: enemies = "DNVP"; workers_dnvp *= 0.89; old_middle_dnvp *= 0.97; new_middle_dnvp *= 0.93; rural_dnvp *= 0.98; dnvp_relation -= 3; dnvp_relation -= 5 if dnvp_line = 1; bvp_relation -= 3

Our anti Nationalist–Monarchist rhetoric calls out this party on their faults and fundamental beliefs as the reasoning for our inability to cooperate on coalition and government affairs.

@nsdap
on-arrival: enemies = "NSDAP"; neorevisionist_strength += 5; nazi_urgency += 1 if nazi_urgency > 0; workers_nsdap -= 4 if nazi_urgency > 0; workers_spd -= 1 if nazi_urgency <= 0

[? if nazi_urgency == 0 or nsdap_r < 10: The NSDAP is a tiny party right now, with more bark than bite. Many in our party are questioning our choices. ?]
[? if nazi_urgency > 0 and nsdap_r >= 10: The Nazis are the most urgent problem for us to deal with. ?]

@kpd
on-arrival: enemies = "KPD"; reformist_strength += 5; left_dissent += 8; reformist_dissent -= 5; kpd_relation -= 15; dvp_relation += 5; z_relation += 5; workers_kpd -= 4 if workers_kpd < 25

Attacking the KPD is supported by all but the most left-wing socialists and wins some approval among bourgeois parties. However, if we want to reconcile with the KPD, this may not be the best choice.

@bourgeois
on-arrival: enemies = "bourgeois parties"; left_strength += 8; left_dissent -= 5; dvp_relation -= 5; z_relation -= 5; kpd_relation += 5; reformist_dissent += 8; workers_z -= 3; workers_dvp -= 2; unemployed_dvp -= 5; new_middle_dvp -= 2; coalition_dissent += 1

Our anti-bourgeois rhetoric is popular among the left, but may make it harder to build coalitions necessary for future government.

@dvp
view-if: sandbox = 1
on-arrival: enemies = "DVP"; left_strenght += 1; dvp_relation -= 7; z_relation -= 2; ddp_relation -= 3; old_middle_spd -= 2; coalition_dissent += 0.5; workers_dvp -= 3; new_middle_dvp -= 1; reformist_dissent += 4; kpd_relation += 1; dnvp_relation -= 2 if dnvp_line = 1

Our anti-industrialist propaganda seeks to undermine the DVP and our relationship with them.

@bvp
view-if: sandbox = 1
on-arrival: enemies = "BVP"; bvp_relation -= 5; z_relation -= 3; old_middle_bvp *= 0.99; workers_bvp *= 0.90; rural_bvp *= 0.98; new_middle_bvp *= 0.95; unemployed_bvp *= 0.80;

We concentrated on attacking the BVP over their conservatism and obstructionism.
